1
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:25,250
（序幕）

2
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:37,750
（极北之地 1857年）

3
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:55,700
船长！
Captain!

4
00:01:01,830 --> 00:01:02,830
船长！
Captain!

5
00:01:04,290 --> 00:01:05,500
能聊聊吗？
Can we talk?

6
00:01:09,370 --> 00:01:10,500
嗯
Hmm.

7
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:14,580
我们必须破冰前行
We must break through the ice.

8
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,040
大家都很饿 也累坏了
The men are hungry and exhausted.

9
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:20,620
要是继续这样下去 恐怕会付出代价
We cannot keep up this pace without consequence.

10
00:01:25,290 --> 00:01:26,580
大家听着！
Listen up, men!

11
00:01:27,870 --> 00:01:32,700
我们拖得越久 冰就冻得越牢固
The more we delay the labor, the firmer the grasp of the ice will become.

12
00:01:33,450 --> 00:01:34,750
继续干活
The work continues.

13
00:01:35,290 --> 00:01:36,700
各组轮流作业
Rotate each group.

14
00:01:36,790 --> 00:01:37,950
先生 请听我说
Sir, with respect…

15
00:01:38,450 --> 00:01:39,910
大家需要一句准话
The men need assurances.

16
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:40,950
准话？
Assurances?

17
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:44,790
对 就是让船动起来之后 我们会回圣彼得堡去
Yes, that we will head back to St. Petersburg once we free the ship.

18
00:01:44,870 --> 00:01:47,580
他们觉得我们的船航行不了多久了 他们想知道…
They don't think we'll be seaworthy for long and they want to know--

19
00:01:47,660 --> 00:01:49,080
都听好了！
Listen up!

20
00:01:50,910 --> 00:01:55,870
别的任何事情 都不是你们和这位长官该考虑的
It is neither your place, nor the officer here, to think anything…

21
00:01:55,950 --> 00:01:59,120
我们接受了一项任务 就要把它完成
We signed up for a mission and we will see it to completion.

22
00:01:59,830 --> 00:02:01,750
我们一定会到达北极
We will reach the North Pole.

23
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,450
都听明白了吗？
Is it understood?

24
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,330
船长 那里爆炸了…
An explosion, Captain.

25
00:02:43,540 --> 00:02:45,080
离这里大约三公里
About two miles away.

26
00:02:51,580 --> 00:02:53,080
去救人
Get the men.

27
00:03:10,790 --> 00:03:12,910
雪橇犬没受伤
The sled dogs are unharmed.

28
00:03:13,410 --> 00:03:15,120
那这血是哪来的？
Then where does all this blood come from?

29
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,620
船长 在那里！
Over here, Captain!

30
00:03:18,370 --> 00:03:20,450
有个受了伤的人 他流了好多血
A wounded man, he's lost a lot of blood.

31
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,910
肩膀受伤了 腿断了
Wound to the shoulder, his leg is broken.

32
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,200
是被熊咬的吗？
Bear attack?

33
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:29,870
我觉得不是 船长
I don't think so, Captain.

34
00:03:29,950 --> 00:03:31,700
拉森 来帮我把这只靴子脱下来
Larsen, help me with his boot.

35
00:03:42,580 --> 00:03:43,950
是个假肢
A prosthetic leg.

36
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,330
把他抬船上去
Put him on the board.

37
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:57,450
快 抬上船 赶紧！
Hurry! To the ship! Now!

38
00:04:02,830 --> 00:04:04,620
拉森 那东西来了
Larsen, that thing is coming.

39
00:04:07,870 --> 00:04:09,540
步枪准备！
Ready the rifles!

40
00:04:14,580 --> 00:04:15,950
听我指令
On my command.

41
00:04:20,580 --> 00:04:21,700
瞄准！
Aim!

42
00:04:22,790 --> 00:04:24,160
开火！
Fire!

43
00:04:35,790 --> 00:04:36,910
下一组！
Next group!

44
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:41,500
开火！
Fire!

45
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,450
全部上船！
All to the ship!!

46
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,040
我们抬上船的那个人呢？
Where is that man we brought onboard?

47
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:19,950
他在哪里？
Where?

48
00:05:20,870 --> 00:05:22,580
那究竟是什么东西？它想干什么？
What is that thing? What does it want?

49
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:34,660
把他给我！
Bring him to me!

50
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,750
喇叭枪 拉森 拿喇叭枪！
The blunderbuss. Larsen, get the blunderbuss!

51
00:06:01,910 --> 00:06:03,410
维克多
Victor.

52
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,160
维克多！
Victor!

53
00:06:19,790 --> 00:06:20,870
我杀了它
I killed it.

54
00:06:21,410 --> 00:06:22,500
我杀了它
I killed it.

55
00:06:35,950 --> 00:06:37,000
它还活着！
It's still alive!

56
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,200
梯子！
Ladder!

57
00:06:38,290 --> 00:06:39,620
快收梯子！
Pull up the ladder!

58
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:58,580
把他交出来！
Bring him to me!

59
00:07:16,790 --> 00:07:18,540
还剩几发？
How many shots are left?

60
00:07:18,620 --> 00:07:20,080
一发 但杀不了它
One, but it can't kill it.

61
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:21,700
我知道
I know.

62
00:07:22,540 --> 00:07:23,870
我也不是要打他
I'm not aiming for him.

63
00:08:15,540 --> 00:08:18,790
这是鸦片酊 能止痛 喝吧
Laudanum, to ease the pain. Drink it. Drink it.

64
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,540
我这是在哪里？
Where am I?

65
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:27,330
这是丹麦皇家航船霍莱松特号
You are on the Royal Danish ship, Horisont.

66
00:08:27,410 --> 00:08:29,250
我是安德森船长 这位是邬德森医生
I'm Captain Anderson. This is Dr. Udsen.

67
00:08:29,330 --> 00:08:31,370
那怪物杀了你们多少人？
How many of your men did it kill?

68
00:08:33,910 --> 00:08:34,750
六个
Six.

69
00:08:34,830 --> 00:08:37,200
它会回来 让更多人丧命
It will come back and kill many more.

70
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:41,750
要是不把我交出去 你们都会没命
All of you, if necessary, unless you deliver me to it.

71
00:08:41,830 --> 00:08:43,450
不会的 它不在了
No, no. It's gone.

72
00:08:43,540 --> 00:08:45,410
它沉入了冰水 死了
It sank in the freezing waters. It's dead.

73
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:47,120
它没死！
No, it is not!

74
00:08:47,660 --> 00:08:48,830
它死不了
It cannot die.

75
00:08:49,450 --> 00:08:51,160
我一直尝试彻底摧毁它
I have tried to destroy it.

76
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:55,410
不管你们信不信
Whether you believe me or not,

77
00:08:57,450 --> 00:09:00,200
它都会回来 找我
it will come back… for me.

78
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,120
等它真的回来了
And when it does,

79
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:06,660
一定要把我送到外面的冰面上
you must promise that you will put me out on the ice

80
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:07,910
让它带走我
and let it take me.

81
00:09:09,290 --> 00:09:10,120
求你们了
Please.

82
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,620
那究竟是什么？
What manner of creature is that?

83
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:16,870
是什么样的魔鬼造出来的？
What manner of devil made him?

84
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,000
是我
I did.

85
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:22,950
就是我
I did.

86
00:09:24,290 --> 00:09:25,500
是我亲手造的他
I made him.

87
00:09:27,870 --> 00:09:32,370
我本已下定决心 让那些罪恶的记忆和我一同消亡
I had determined that the memory of my evils should die with me.

88
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,160
准备好了
It's ready.

89
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:37,580
接下来我要说的话 有些是真的
Some of what I will tell you is fact.

90
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:42,580
有些是假的 但这是真的
Some is not, but it is all true.

91
00:09:42,660 --> 00:09:44,790
我叫维克多
My name is Victor.

92
00:09:45,370 --> 00:09:46,790
维克多·弗兰肯斯坦
Victor Frankenstein.

93
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:51,000
我的名字是父亲起的
It was my father who gave me that name.

94
00:09:51,830 --> 00:09:53,330
你知道这名字是什么意思吗？
Do you know what it means?

95
00:09:53,410 --> 00:09:55,790
应该是征服者的意思
I believe I do, yes. Conqueror.

96
00:09:56,580 --> 00:09:57,750
赢得一切的人
One that wins it all.

97
00:09:57,830 --> 00:09:59,870
没错 一切因他而起
Yes. It all started with him.

98
00:10:00,450 --> 00:10:01,370
我的父亲
My father.

99
00:10:04,290 --> 00:10:05,330
还有我的母亲
And my mother.

100
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:10,450
维克多！
Victor!

101
00:10:10,540 --> 00:10:12,580
（第一部分 维克多的故事）

102
00:10:12,660 --> 00:10:13,500
维克多！
Victor!

103
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:17,250
维克多！
Victor!

104
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:23,830
快下来 你父亲来了
Come down, your father is arriving.

105
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:27,750
Maman?
Maman?

106
00:10:28,950 --> 00:10:30,370
母亲 我在这里
I'm here, Mother.

107
00:10:33,910 --> 00:10:35,120
这里
I'm here.

108
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:41,410
我父亲是男爵 也是个杰出的外科医生
My father was a baron and a preeminent surgeon.

109
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,660
他娶我母亲 很大程度上为了利益
He had married my mother largely out of convenience,

110
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:47,750
因为母亲的陪嫁相当丰厚 而且她是贵族出身
as her dowry was considerable and her lineage noble.

111
00:10:47,830 --> 00:10:53,200
她带来的资金 足以让父亲维持爵位和家族产业
It furnished my father with the means to preserve his rank and family estate.

112
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:08,000
日常生活中 从来看不见父亲的身影
He was absent from our lives,

113
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:11,000
而每当他回到家 所有人都对他唯命是从
but when he came home, the entire household bent to his will.

114
00:11:11,540 --> 00:11:12,660
亲爱的克莱尔
Claire, dear.

115
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:14,370
他不在的时候…
The rest of the time…

116
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:16,160
维克多
Victor.

117
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:17,250
父亲
Father.

118
00:11:17,330 --> 00:11:19,500
他不在的时候 母亲就是我一个人的
The rest of the time, Mother was mine.

119
00:11:27,290 --> 00:11:29,540
别拿走 端到这里来
No, bring that here.

120
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:39,160
肉里的盐分能滋养你的血液
The salts in the meat will enrich your blood,

121
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:40,540
还有胎儿的
as well as the baby's.

122
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:42,790
一人吃 两人补 记得吗？
You eat for two, remember?

123
00:11:53,950 --> 00:11:54,950
吃吧
Go on.

124
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,120
很有营养
It's nutritious.

125
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:04,500
守护天使
Guardian angel.

126
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:06,500
甜蜜的陪伴
Sweet companion.

127
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,410
请守护我 不要离开我
Stand by my side and do not leave me.

128
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:13,160
用你的披风庇护我 然后…
Under your mantle, shelter me, and…

129
00:12:15,580 --> 00:12:18,700
我隔着墙听到他们争论不休
I would hear them through the wall, arguing incessantly,

130
00:12:18,790 --> 00:12:22,620
对着彼此大吼大叫 话题关于财富和庄园 还有我
yelling at each other about wealth, estate… and me.

131
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:26,330
他们的争吵声让我万分恐惧
Their voices filled me with fear.

132
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:32,080
Maman?
Maman?

133
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,200
Maman?
Maman?

134
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:48,200
那个男人鄙视我们两个
The man despised us both.

135
00:12:48,290 --> 00:12:52,120
讨厌我们乌黑的头发、深色的瞳孔
Our raven black hair, our deep, dark eyes.

136
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:56,790
就连我们喜好安静、不时紧张的性情
Even our quiet, at times nervous disposition

137
00:12:56,870 --> 00:12:59,580
似乎也会让他大为光火
seemed to exasperate him to no end.

138
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:05,000
古代把体液分为哪几类？
List as accurately as you can the ancient classification

139
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:07,370
尽量说精确一点
of the humors in the human body.

140
00:13:07,450 --> 00:13:11,700
血液、黑胆汁、黄胆汁和黏液
Blood, black bile, yellow bile, and phlegm.

141
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:15,200
男性心脏的平均重量是多少？
Average male heart. Weight?

142
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,830
250到310克 父亲
Nine to eleven ounces, Father.

143
00:13:19,540 --> 00:13:21,950
女性心脏的平均重量？
Average female heart. Weight?

144
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:24,410
230到280克
Eight to ten ounces.

145
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,870
你为什么觉得
Why do you suppose that is?

146
00:13:27,540 --> 00:13:29,750
女性的心脏会轻一点？
Difference in mass in female heart?

147
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:31,660
是因为她们情感更强烈？
Depth of emotion?

148
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:33,950
更容易忧郁吗？
Tendency to the melancholic?

149
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:39,500
因为质量 血流量 肌肉灌注的不同 父亲
Mass. Volume of blood, Father. Muscular irrigation.

150
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:43,330
没错 人体组织中没有精神物质
Quite. There is no spiritual content in tissue,

151
00:13:43,410 --> 00:13:45,290
肌肉中没有情感
and no emotion in a muscle.

152
00:13:45,370 --> 00:13:48,790
那么 请描述一下三尖瓣的主要功能
Now, describe the main function of the tricuspid valve, please.

153
00:13:51,620 --> 00:13:54,750
我现在想不起来了 父亲 但我肯定能想起来
I cannot recall, Father, but I'm sure I will remember.

154
00:13:54,830 --> 00:13:56,250
嗯 我相信你
Yeah, I'm sure you will.

155
00:13:56,950 --> 00:13:59,000
象牙不会流血 维克多
Ivory does not bleed, Victor.

156
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,330
但人体会
Flesh does.

157
00:14:01,330 --> 00:14:04,330
等你想起了某个知识要点 恐怕你的病人已经一命呜呼了
By the time you remember a fact, your patient could be dead.

158
00:14:04,410 --> 00:14:05,790
懂了吗？
You understand?

159
00:14:10,290 --> 00:14:13,330
三尖瓣的主要功能
The main function of the tricuspid valve

160
00:14:13,830 --> 00:14:16,910
是防止血液反流至腔静脉
is to prevent the reflux of blood into the vena cava.

161
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:22,910
不打手了 再也不打了
No, not your hands. Not anymore.

162
00:14:23,950 --> 00:14:26,580
它们如今是你施展技艺的工具 是你意志的延伸
They are now the instruments of your craft and will,

163
00:14:27,620 --> 00:14:29,040
要好好保护
and we must care for them.

164
00:14:31,870 --> 00:14:34,660
而你的脸 就微不足道了
Your face, however, is vanity.

165
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:46,830
维克多 你沿用了我的名字 也必然要维护我的名声
You bear my name, Victor, and with it my reputation.

166
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:52,500
我恳请你牢记这一点
I pray you remember that.

167
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:00,580
我感觉你有很好的牌
I feel you have something very good, parce que…

168
00:15:01,830 --> 00:15:03,080
三
Three…

169
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,410
二
Two…

170
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:05,370
一
One…

171
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,700
不可能
That's impossible.

172
00:15:10,450 --> 00:15:11,450
我来洗牌
I'll shuffle.

173
00:15:17,330 --> 00:15:18,450
母亲？
Mother?

174
00:15:19,620 --> 00:15:21,000
Maman?\Maman?

175
00:15:26,620 --> 00:15:27,950
父亲
Father!

176
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:29,450
父亲 母亲出事了
Father. It's Mother.

177
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,700
Maman.\Maman.

178
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:40,540
准备好热水和干净的亚麻布 多拿一点 快
I need hot water and clean linen. A lot of it.

179
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:41,450
是 先生
-Now. -Sir.

180
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:42,540
-不 维克多 -妈妈？
-No, Victor! -Mother?

181
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:45,500
-Maman! -维克多!
-Maman! -Victor!

182
00:15:49,330 --> 00:15:51,870
父亲！
Father! Father!

183
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:53,410
一定要救她 求你了！
-Victor! -Save her, please!

184
00:16:35,910 --> 00:16:41,120
我的母亲 我曾将她视作我的一部分
My mother, whom I had come to consider a part of my very self,

185
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,500
我曾以为她永远不会离去
she who I thought would never leave,

186
00:16:45,370 --> 00:16:49,330
以为她是我的生命 如今她死了
she who was life… was now death.

187
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:52,830
她的双眼已暗淡无光
Her eyes extinguished,

188
00:16:53,830 --> 00:16:57,040
笑容被冰冷的土地埋葬
her smile feeding the cold earth.

189
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,500
走开！
Leave!

190
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:07,200
都给我走开！
All of you, leave!

191
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,950
我的世界空了一块
A part of the universe had been hollowed out

192
00:17:19,120 --> 00:17:22,830
我的头顶笼罩着永远的黑暗
and the firmament was now permanently dark.

193
00:17:24,540 --> 00:17:26,040
遮住眼睛
Now, cover your eyes.

194
00:17:28,370 --> 00:17:30,790
我叫你看再看哦
Don't look until I tell you to.

195
00:17:32,620 --> 00:17:33,620
看吧
Now.

196
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:36,790
威廉在阳光和笑容中长大
William grew full of sunshine and smiles.

197
00:17:36,870 --> 00:17:41,540
他的性情比我平和温顺 显然更讨父亲喜欢
He was of a calmer, gentler disposition, clearly favored by my father.

198
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:43,660
谢谢你 父亲
Thank you, Father.

199
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:45,410
不客气 儿子
Oh, it's a pleasure, my boy.

200
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:49,580
他是宜人的微风 我是滚滚的黑云
He was the breeze, I was the storm cloud.

201
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:53,870
他带来欢声笑语 我让人愁眉不展
He was all laughter, I was all frowns.

202
00:17:53,950 --> 00:17:55,000
拿起缰绳
Pick up the reins.

203
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:58,370
父亲 看我做得怎么样
Look at me, Father. Look at me.

204
00:17:59,790 --> 00:18:01,450
不止如此
There was something more.

205
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:05,290
更确切地说 某些东西被忽视了
Or rather, something was missing.

206
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:09,080
我的母亲
My mother had died

207
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:12,620
死在如日中天的名医
at the hands of the most distinguished doctor of his day:

208
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:13,870
我的父亲手下
My father.

209
00:18:14,910 --> 00:18:18,700
我的脑中渐渐有了个想法
An idea… took shape in my mind.

210
00:18:19,330 --> 00:18:21,450
请说说《心血运动论》中…
Define the circulatory system, if you will…

211
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:24,620
无可避免 无法逃避
Inevitable, unavoidable…

212
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:28,200
…对循环系统是怎么定义的
…as enunciated in De Motu Cordis.

213
00:18:28,290 --> 00:18:30,040
…直到这个想法被说了出来
…until it became truth.

214
00:18:30,540 --> 00:18:31,450
父亲？
Father?

215
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:36,950
你没救她 对吗？
You let her die, did you not?

216
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:41,120
我用尽全力救她了 你必须知道这一点
I did everything in my power to save her. You must know that.

217
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,410
这么说 你失败了
So you failed.

218
00:18:43,370 --> 00:18:45,620
没人能战胜死亡
-No one can conquer death. -Mm-hmm.

219
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:52,540
我能 我会战胜的
I will. I will conquer it.

220
00:18:54,290 --> 00:18:57,330
我会掌握你掌握的所有知识 还会更进一步
Everything you know, I will know. And more.

221
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:01,120
今天就到此为止吧
I think we've done quite enough for today.

222
00:19:03,830 --> 00:19:06,160
那晚我重生了
I was born anew that night.

223
00:19:06,830 --> 00:19:08,290
我看到了幻象
I had a vision.

224
00:19:09,370 --> 00:19:12,540
我第一次看到了
I saw, for the first time…

225
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:14,830
黑暗天使
the Dark Angel.

226
00:19:28,830 --> 00:19:30,410
它向我许下承诺
And it made me a promise.

227
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:35,790
我将能掌控生死
I would have command over the forces of life and death.

228
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:40,250
成为和父亲一样杰出的外科医生
I would become every ounce the surgeon my father was.

229
00:19:40,330 --> 00:19:43,500
我的野心和成就将超过他
I would surpass him in ambition and in reach.

230
00:19:43,580 --> 00:19:44,870
守护天使…

231
00:19:45,620 --> 00:19:46,910
幻象如此清晰
The vision was so clear.

232
00:19:47,660 --> 00:19:51,290
无论清醒还是睡梦中 我都从未看到如此清晰的景象
Clearer than anything I'd ever seen in my waking hours or dreams.

233
00:19:54,910 --> 00:19:55,870
但承诺如何兑现？
But how?

234
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:21,200
我的境遇很快一落千丈
My downfall was swift.

235
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:25,950
母亲的种植园 经历了两次叛乱和一场火灾
Two revolts and a fire on my mother's plantations

236
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:27,620
家族财富因此锐减
dwindled the family fortune.

237
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:31,200
庄园留下了 但别的全都没了
We kept the estate, but lost everything else.

238
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:49,580
威廉被送去了维也纳的亲戚家
William went to one side of the family in Vienna

239
00:20:49,660 --> 00:20:51,910
我去了伦敦 然后又去了爱丁堡
and I to London, then Edinburgh.

240
00:20:52,830 --> 00:20:56,620
在那里 我花了数十年时间
And there, for decades, I tried to…

241
00:20:58,870 --> 00:21:02,120
尝试为狭隘的学术界拓宽边界
expand the narrow limits of academia.

242
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:05,000
生命
Life.

243
00:21:06,620 --> 00:21:10,500
这就是生命 先生们
This… is life, gentlemen.

244
00:21:10,580 --> 00:21:12,700
（皇家医学院纪律法庭 1855年）

245
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:13,950
我们出生了
We are born.

246
00:21:14,620 --> 00:21:15,500
嗯?
Hmm?

247
00:21:15,580 --> 00:21:18,410
刚上去没多久 就掉下来了
And no sooner do we rise, we fall.

248
00:21:19,410 --> 00:21:20,500
死了
Death.

249
00:21:22,450 --> 00:21:25,910
这一起一落之间
And in the space between that rise and fall,

250
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,830
就是我们渺小卑微的一生
our humble little purview.

251
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:31,870
出生不为我们所控
Now, birth is not in our hands.

252
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,000
对不对？
Is it?

253
00:21:35,450 --> 00:21:40,000
生命之火的点燃 思想和灵魂的诞生
Conception, that spark, the animation of thought and soul.

254
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,370
掌握在上帝的手中
That is in God's hands.

255
00:21:43,330 --> 00:21:44,250
上帝
God.

256
00:21:45,330 --> 00:21:46,410
而死亡
But death.

257
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:49,660
挑战正在此处
Ah, now there lies the challenge.

258
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,950
死亡应该掌握在我们手中
That should be our concern.

259
00:21:53,290 --> 00:21:54,370
应该如此
It should be.

260
00:21:55,580 --> 00:21:58,790
我们凭什么能掌控？ 我们又不是神明 对不对？
Who are we to do so? We are not gods, are we?

261
00:21:59,410 --> 00:22:02,660
但要是我们能像神明那般大胆
But if we are to behave as immodestly as gods,

262
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:05,620
那至少能够创造奇迹
we must, at the very least, deliver miracles.

263
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:07,250
是不是？
Wouldn't you say?

264
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:12,450
在年轻学子心中点燃神圣火花
Ignite a divine spark…in these young students' minds.

265
00:22:12,540 --> 00:22:15,700
教导他们抛弃顺从 违抗权威
Teach them defiance rather than obedience.

266
00:22:15,790 --> 00:22:21,450
展示人类有可能掌控自然奥秘 让死亡不再发生
Show that man may pursue nature to her hiding places and stop death.

267
00:22:21,540 --> 00:22:24,450
不是延缓死亡 而是长生不老！
Not slow it down, but stop it entirely!

268
00:22:30,580 --> 00:22:33,370
安静！
Silence. Silence!

269
00:22:36,910 --> 00:22:42,330
这种不可能的事 你究竟要怎么教？
How exactly do you propose to teach what is impossible?

270
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,160
人类的尸体 一个复合实体
Composite subject, the body.

271
00:22:48,250 --> 00:22:51,370
这是某个店老板 刚咽气没多久就送到了我这里
That of a shopkeeper, delivered mere moments after expiration.

272
00:22:51,950 --> 00:22:53,540
大脑暴露在外 但仍能运作
The brain laid bare but functional,

273
00:22:53,620 --> 00:22:56,160
脊神经分支和迷走神经完好无损
the spinal branches and vagal nerves intact.

274
00:22:56,700 --> 00:22:59,040
大家或许能看到一些极细的伤口
You may observe the hair-thin scars.

275
00:22:59,120 --> 00:23:01,750
我的手艺无需粗糙的缝合
No coarse stitching needed by my own technique.

276
00:23:01,830 --> 00:23:03,000
看这条手臂
The arm, you see,

277
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:05,620
来自某个木匠
comes from another specimen, that of a carpenter.

278
00:23:05,700 --> 00:23:08,830
肌肉、韧带、神经 都已连结好
The muscles, ligaments, nerves, all connected now.

279
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:32,040
看啊 电流导致躯体痉挛
Now, the spasmodic movement of the body

280
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:34,120
这已不是新鲜事
caused from the electric current, this is not new.

281
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:37,700
大家都见过 不过 这种躯体内的能量流动
It's not new. However, the flow of energy through the body

282
00:23:37,790 --> 00:23:39,370
遵循一种完全不同的概念
follows a different notion entirely.

283
00:23:39,450 --> 00:23:41,290
一种称为气的东方概念
An Eastern notion called qi.

284
00:23:41,910 --> 00:23:45,120
这种概念认为 生命能量的流动 同时存在于身体内外
Now, it considers the vital flow of energy both within and without.

285
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,870
我用针在六个…
I'm utilizing needles in six--

286
00:23:46,950 --> 00:23:51,040
安静！都坐下！
Quiet! Sit down!

287
00:23:52,750 --> 00:23:56,040
医生 这是听证会 不是狂欢节表演
This is a hearing, Doctor, not a carnival act.

288
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:58,080
你这样无济于事 维克多
You're not helping your cause, Victor.

289
00:23:58,160 --> 00:24:00,750
这种用电的诡计根本没用
This galvanic trickery will simply not do.

290
00:24:00,830 --> 00:24:01,830
诡计
Trickery.

291
00:24:03,750 --> 00:24:04,750
诡计？
Trickery?

292
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:08,160
你确定吗？
Are you sure?

293
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:15,750
这不是诡计 而是一种抉择
That is not trickery. That is a decision.

294
00:24:15,830 --> 00:24:20,160
一个死人的眼睛 和另一个死人的胳膊协调运动
Motor coordination between the eye of one dead man and the arm of another,

295
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:23,790
注入全新的意志和基本的理解力
infused with a new will and the rudiments of understanding.

296
00:24:23,870 --> 00:24:27,500
已经死亡的大脑也有理解力吗？
Understanding in a brain that already died?

297
00:24:28,540 --> 00:24:29,660
放开
Release now.

298
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:31,870
请放开
Please.

299
00:24:33,450 --> 00:24:34,660
礼貌一点总有效果
"Please" always helps.

300
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:39,160
赶紧关了吧 你个江湖骗子
Turn that off at once. At once, you charlatan.

301
00:24:39,250 --> 00:24:42,120
这就是未来 这是有可能实现的
This is the future. This is possible.

302
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:44,290
为什么不研究一下 量化一下呢？
Why not study it? Why not quantify it?

303
00:24:44,370 --> 00:24:50,660
这是罪恶的 可恨、下流！
This is unholy. An abomination. An obscenity!

304
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:55,910
生命由上帝赐予 由上帝收回 维克多
God gives life, and God takes it, Victor.

305
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:58,500
或许上帝就是无能！
Perhaps God is inept!

306
00:24:59,910 --> 00:25:02,330
要由我们来纠正他的错误！
And it is we that must amend his mistakes!

307
00:25:02,410 --> 00:25:04,950
别让这些老蠢货阻止你自由表达！
Do not let these old fools extinguish your voice!

308
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:08,410
只有采取不盲从的态度 摆脱恐惧和恃强凌弱的教条
The answers only come when coaxed by disobedience,

309
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:11,410
答案才会浮现！
free of fear and cowardly dogma!

310
00:25:25,870 --> 00:25:27,160
克伦佩教授
Professor Krempe.

311
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:05,870
弗兰肯斯坦男爵 我叫海因里希·哈兰德
Baron Frankenstein, my name is Heinrich Harlander,

312
00:26:05,950 --> 00:26:08,700
我这里有一封
and I carry with me a letter of introduction

313
00:26:08,790 --> 00:26:10,160
你的弟弟威廉写的介绍信
from your brother, William.

314
00:26:10,250 --> 00:26:11,200
我弟弟？
From my brother?

315
00:26:11,290 --> 00:26:13,660
我希望能有幸认识你
I asked for the privilege of your acquaintance.

316
00:26:13,750 --> 00:26:15,620
耽误你一点时间
It won't take but a minute of your time.

317
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:16,870
-请进 -好
-Please. -Very well.

318
00:26:19,580 --> 00:26:21,700
这么说 威廉要来看我 对吗？
So William is coming to see me, is that it?

319
00:26:22,450 --> 00:26:24,160
对 几天后到
Yeah, in a matter of days.

320
00:26:24,870 --> 00:26:29,120
他想让你见见他的未婚妻 也就是我的侄女
He wants to introduce you to his fiancée. My niece, as it happens.

321
00:26:33,410 --> 00:26:36,200
她叫伊丽莎白·哈兰德 是一位非常可爱的小姐
Elizabeth Harlander, a very nice young lady,

322
00:26:36,290 --> 00:26:37,540
刚刚从修道院学校毕业
fresh from convent life.

323
00:26:38,410 --> 00:26:39,410
这些照片都是我拍的
The photographs are mine.

324
00:26:39,910 --> 00:26:43,040
威廉在金融领域很有成就
William has become quite successful in the world of finance.

325
00:26:43,120 --> 00:26:44,830
弗兰肯斯坦的名声越来越响了
He's making a name for himself.

326
00:26:44,910 --> 00:26:47,000
哎哟！是吗？
Ha! A name? For himself?

327
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:52,540
要知道我们都是弗兰肯斯坦 不管我们乐不乐意
Well, I'm afraid we both share that name, whether we like it or not.

328
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:54,830
我拜读了你在《柳叶刀》上的文章
I read your article in The Lancet.

329
00:26:55,370 --> 00:26:57,160
你真的觉得这事能做到吗？
You really believe you can do it?

330
00:26:58,290 --> 00:26:59,370
组装出一个人来？
Assemble a man?

331
00:27:00,580 --> 00:27:03,450
做出完整的全新人体？还要有生命？
A full new body? And give it life?

332
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:06,200
你今天也看到了
You saw it today, didn't you?

333
00:27:06,290 --> 00:27:08,620
说真的 我看到的是你当众受难
What I saw was a crucifixion, really.

334
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:11,330
你还没开口说句话 就被钉死了
You were done for before you uttered a word.

335
00:27:11,410 --> 00:27:12,750
但我还是向他们展示了
I still showed them.

336
00:27:13,870 --> 00:27:14,700
展示什么？
What?

337
00:27:14,790 --> 00:27:15,620
事实
The truth.

338
00:27:16,410 --> 00:27:18,080
他们到晚餐时间就忘了
They will forget by suppertime.

339
00:27:19,500 --> 00:27:21,950
话虽如此 你觉得怎么样？
Yes, yes, yes. But what did you think? Hmm?

340
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:25,620
我觉得非常厉害
I thought it was brilliant.

341
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:28,160
没错 我就知道
It was. I know.

342
00:27:28,250 --> 00:27:31,040
但你有点孩子气 太激动了
But you are like a child, so excited,

343
00:27:31,120 --> 00:27:34,200
紧抓你的新宠物 快把它勒死了
clutching your new pet so tightly that you're strangling it.

344
00:27:35,500 --> 00:27:37,450
我不免为你担心
That is why I worry about you.

345
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:41,160
你能控制好火种吗 普罗米修斯？
Can you contain your fire, Prometheus?

346
00:27:41,250 --> 00:27:44,120
还是没等把它交出去 就先烧伤了自己的手？
Or are you going to burn your hands before delivering it?

347
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:47,410
说得对
Quite.

348
00:27:48,410 --> 00:27:51,910
请不要觉得我无礼 但这一天已经足够漫长
Please do not think me rude, but my day has proven long enough,

349
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:55,040
我的状态也完全不适合 再陪伴陌生人了
and I believe myself totally unfit for the company of strangers.

350
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:56,620
如果没有什么别的事了…
So if there's nothing more--

351
00:27:56,700 --> 00:27:58,620
还有重要的事
Oh, but there is. Much more.

352
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:03,660
我在爱丁堡找好了住处
I've taken quarters in Edinburgh.

353
00:28:03,750 --> 00:28:07,160
三天后 我们一起见威廉和伊丽莎白
Three days from now, we are to meet with William and Elizabeth.

354
00:28:07,250 --> 00:28:10,370
我将在那晚改变你的命运
And that evening, I will change your destiny.

355
00:28:11,700 --> 00:28:14,000
我会让你看到非同凡响的东西
I will show you something extraordinary.

356
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:24,500
-你真好 -谢谢 给

357
00:28:31,410 --> 00:28:35,160
桃子 把桃子转过来
The peach. The peach. Turn the peach. Turn it.

358
00:28:36,700 --> 00:28:38,330
你又啃了
You bit it again.

359
00:28:39,330 --> 00:28:40,830
你一直在吃桃
You're eating the peaches.

360
00:28:41,500 --> 00:28:43,330
这是对死亡的沉思
This is a memento mori.

361
00:28:44,040 --> 00:28:49,410
桃子是生命和青春的符号 怎么就被你啃了？
The peach, symbol of life and youth, and you bite into it?

362
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:51,700
-我饿了呀 小希 -别那样叫我
-I was hungry, Kiki. -Don't call me Kiki.

363
00:28:51,790 --> 00:28:53,660
先生 维克多·弗兰肯斯坦男爵来了
Baron Victor Frankenstein, sir.

364
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:56,910
你可以下去了
You can leave.

365
00:28:57,660 --> 00:28:58,750
抱歉
Forgive me.

366
00:29:00,330 --> 00:29:01,200
欢迎
Welcome.

367
00:29:01,290 --> 00:29:02,250
哈兰德先生
Herr Harlander.

368
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:05,870
这是一种新兴艺术 摄影
A young art, photography.

369
00:29:05,950 --> 00:29:07,330
再见 小希
Goodbye, Kiki.

370
00:29:07,410 --> 00:29:09,160
我已经迷上了
Already a passion of mine.

371
00:29:09,750 --> 00:29:11,080
文件都带来了吗？
Did you bring the papers?

372
00:29:12,540 --> 00:29:13,580
谢谢
Oh, thank you.

373
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:19,370
-你非常出色 -谢谢
-You're extraordinary. -Thank you.

374
00:29:20,580 --> 00:29:21,540
嗯
Hmm.

375
00:29:23,370 --> 00:29:27,620
你利用神经系统来传递能量脉冲
You're using the nervous system to deliver the surge of energy.

376
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:29,660
对吗？
Are you not?

377
00:29:29,750 --> 00:29:30,910
没错
Correct.

378
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:35,000
因此 你所操控的生命力 只能维持很短时间
And thus the sustainability of the life force you command

379
00:29:35,080 --> 00:29:38,370
很快就会衰退、消散
is very brief, wanes, evaporates.

380
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,000
为什么这么说？
How so?

381
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:48,620
当时你颇为自豪地结束了演示
At the lecture, you ended your demonstration out of pride.

382
00:29:51,410 --> 00:29:53,660
但其实是因为 那股电流般的生命力
But really, because the galvanic life force

383
00:29:53,750 --> 00:29:55,500
已经衰竭了 对吗？
was already fading, was it not?

384
00:29:55,580 --> 00:29:57,200
先生 你是外科医生吗？
Are you yourself a surgeon, sir?

385
00:29:57,700 --> 00:30:00,040
曾经是 我是战地医生
Yeah, once upon a time. An army surgeon.

386
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:02,700
医术也说不上多精湛
Not a particularly skilled one, either.

387
00:30:02,790 --> 00:30:05,950
但也给我打下了发家致富的基础
But it allowed me to secure the rudiments of my fortune.

388
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,950
我现在有几家军火工厂
I own a few ammunition factories.

389
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:10,870
-你是军火商 -不如说是个务实的
-An arms merchant. -A realist.

390
00:30:11,450 --> 00:30:13,330
你对伊夫林解剖图表熟悉吗？
Are you familiar with the Evelyn Tables?

391
00:30:13,410 --> 00:30:15,950
当然 那是约翰·伊夫林爵士当年
Of course. Acquired by Sir John Evelyn,

392
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:18,000
买下的四张人体标本精细解剖图
there are four planks, meticulous dissection,

393
00:30:18,080 --> 00:30:20,120
是欧洲最早的人体神经 和动静脉解剖图
some of the oldest in Europe, presenting the nerves,

394
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:22,080
为什么会提到这个？
veins and arteries of cadavers. What?

395
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:24,000
因为还有第五张
Yes. But there's a fifth one.

396
00:30:24,910 --> 00:30:26,290
这张最让人信服
The most compelling one.

397
00:30:30,330 --> 00:30:33,000
非常细致 是不是？
Exquisite, is it not?

398
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:36,580
呈现于木头上的鲜活血肉
Flesh rendered onto wood.

399
00:30:38,290 --> 00:30:41,580
尸体放在木板上 逐层剥离
The cadaver lies on the plank, is peeled away layer by layer,

400
00:30:41,660 --> 00:30:45,370
用树脂将剩下的组织固定在木板上
and the remaining tissue is lacquered with resin onto the wood.

401
00:30:45,450 --> 00:30:48,750
-这是淋巴系统 -没错
-It showcases the lymphatic system. -Yes.

402
00:30:48,830 --> 00:30:52,620
穆斯林医学家称其为隐秘的循环系统
Muslim medics called it the secret circulatory system.

403
00:30:52,700 --> 00:30:58,200
仅仅输送三升体液 却构成了庞大的网络
It moves a mere three liters of fluid, but it's a vast network.

404
00:30:58,290 --> 00:31:00,000
-真是非同凡响 -确实
-Oh, it's remarkable. -Yes.

405
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:05,160
现在对我们 也是对你而言 关键的改变就在这里
Now for us, for you, the important variation is here.

406
00:31:06,620 --> 00:31:10,290
这第九种构造 环绕心脏的结构
The ninth configuration. A very delicate,

407
00:31:10,370 --> 00:31:13,750
极为精巧 近乎空灵
almost ethereal structure surrounding the heart.

408
00:31:13,830 --> 00:31:17,120
既能分配能量 也能储存能量
It can distribute, but also store energy.

409
00:31:20,790 --> 00:31:23,250
如果你能在不破坏周围组织的前提下
Yes, if you can access that without destroying

410
00:31:23,330 --> 00:31:25,870
-触达这一构造… -不 不是前面
-the surrounding tissue-- -No. Not through the front.

411
00:31:25,950 --> 00:31:29,250
是后面 脊柱 胸曲
The back, spinal column, thoracic curvature.

412
00:31:29,950 --> 00:31:30,830
没错
Of course.

413
00:31:30,910 --> 00:31:36,330
远超人们想象的能量流动 瘢痕形成和组织再生
Flow of energy, scarring and regeneration beyond anyone's imagination.

414
00:31:36,410 --> 00:31:37,700
永生
Life eternal.

415
00:31:39,700 --> 00:31:43,040
我将提供无限的资源 来支持你的研究
I will endow your pursuit with unlimited resources.

416
00:31:45,790 --> 00:31:47,250
那我要拿什么来交换？
And in exchange?

417
00:31:48,750 --> 00:31:50,200
这么说就俗了
No need to become indelicate.

418
00:31:51,250 --> 00:31:54,750
我们探寻真理 志在超越 有着共同的追求
We're searchers for truth and transcendence, kindred spirits.

419
00:31:56,410 --> 00:31:58,370
某天我也许会请你帮个忙 作为回报
I may in time ask you for a favor in return,

420
00:31:58,450 --> 00:32:02,450
但最重要的是记录研究过程 以传诸后世的这份特权
but it's mostly the privilege to record your process for posterity.

421
00:32:02,540 --> 00:32:03,660
我习惯独自工作
I work alone.

422
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,160
我绝对不出声
I'm very quiet.

423
00:32:06,250 --> 00:32:09,250
哈兰德先生 威廉·弗兰肯斯坦和您的侄女到了
William Frankenstein and your niece, Herr Harlander.

424
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:14,200
我要考虑一下
I shall consider it.

425
00:32:15,540 --> 00:32:16,620
我会考虑的
I'll consider it.

426
00:32:17,950 --> 00:32:18,910
男爵
Baron.

427
00:32:20,120 --> 00:32:23,200
别假装冷静了 错过了就可惜了
Don't pretend to be reasonable now. It would be such a shame.

428
00:32:33,620 --> 00:32:34,950
维克多
Victor.

429
00:32:35,040 --> 00:32:36,160
威廉！
William!

430
00:32:36,250 --> 00:32:38,700
-维克多 -瞧瞧你
-Victor. -Look at you.

431
00:32:39,950 --> 00:32:41,620
老天 你长大了
My, you've grown.

432
00:32:41,700 --> 00:32:43,200
可惜不是我的功劳
Through no merit of my own.

433
00:32:44,040 --> 00:32:46,040
来见见我的未婚妻吧
May I introduce the woman I'm to marry.

434
00:32:46,700 --> 00:32:48,250
伊丽莎白·哈兰德小姐
Lady Elizabeth Harlander.

435
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:11,450
荣幸之至
Absolutely delighted.

436
00:33:16,950 --> 00:33:19,250
听到你被驱逐 说实话我也不惊讶
Can't say I was shocked when you were expelled,

437
00:33:19,870 --> 00:33:22,450
但他们的态度太强硬 言语太狠毒
but the manner and virulence of your expulsion,

438
00:33:22,540 --> 00:33:23,700
我认为实在没有必要
uncalled for, I'm sure.

439
00:33:23,790 --> 00:33:24,910
有必要
No, it was called for.

440
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,000
我应得的
I earned it.

441
00:33:26,500 --> 00:33:29,000
我特意挣来的 你说是不是 哈兰德先生？
I made it a point to earn it, wouldn't you say, Herr Harlander?

442
00:33:29,080 --> 00:33:30,660
确实声势浩大
It was quite an exit, I assure you.

443
00:33:32,330 --> 00:33:33,410
为什么要激怒他们？
Why provoke them?

444
00:33:33,500 --> 00:33:37,410
何不继续做自己的事 避免惹来不必要的关注？
Why not just carry on without calling attention to yourself in such a manner?

445
00:33:37,950 --> 00:33:41,120
威廉 就算以你的标准来看 这么做也太保守了
How safe, even by your standards, William.

446
00:33:41,700 --> 00:33:43,250
你这话听着都有点像父亲了
You almost sound like Father.

447
00:33:44,660 --> 00:33:47,120
父亲可是相当老练的
He was a most tactful man, our father.

448
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:50,830
他做事精准、谨慎、有分寸感
He was precise, discreet, measured.

449
00:33:50,910 --> 00:33:55,370
我就不是 我完全不懂为何谦虚是一种美德
I, on the other hand, fail to see why modesty is considered a virtue at all.

450
00:33:55,450 --> 00:33:57,750
维克多一直这么引人注目
Victor's always been one to harvest attention.

451
00:33:58,330 --> 00:34:01,620
即便在小时候 我也常常 通过保持沉默 来消解他的声音
Even as children, I mitigated his voice by staying silent.

452
00:34:01,700 --> 00:34:04,580
这样的事发生无数次了吧 维克多 你说呢？
Perhaps too much and far too many times, wouldn't you say, Victor?

453
00:34:04,660 --> 00:34:06,410
如果可以再造生命
If life can be regenerated,

454
00:34:06,950 --> 00:34:08,200
并非简单的模拟
not as a mere simulation,

455
00:34:08,290 --> 00:34:12,200
而是通过物理化学手段 如神迹般地再造 何不大声说出来？
but as a divine act by physical, chemical means, why whisper it?

456
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:16,870
你笑了？
You laugh?

457
00:34:17,370 --> 00:34:19,700
-你觉得好笑吗？ -没错
-You're amused? -I must be, yes.

458
00:34:19,790 --> 00:34:21,120
我的理念没表达清楚吗？
Are my ideas not clear?

459
00:34:21,200 --> 00:34:23,660
你显然已经够大声的了
You certainly expressed them loudly enough.

460
00:34:23,750 --> 00:34:25,000
不值得为之努力吗？
Are they not worthwhile?

461
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:27,830
我认为理念本身并不值得为之努力
Ideas are not worthwhile by themselves, I don't believe.

462
00:34:30,250 --> 00:34:31,660
愿闻其详
Enlighten me, please.

463
00:34:32,160 --> 00:34:34,370
拿战争来说
Take the war, for example.

464
00:34:34,450 --> 00:34:37,080
威廉 去书房享用雪茄和白兰地吧
William, cigar and brandy in my study?

465
00:34:37,580 --> 00:34:41,200
我侄女的长篇大论你肯定都听过了
Surely you've heard my niece expound on the matter before.

466
00:34:42,410 --> 00:34:43,450
我们失陪了
You'll excuse us.

467
00:34:48,290 --> 00:34:50,500
请继续说 关于理念
Pray, carry on. Ideas.

468
00:34:51,450 --> 00:34:57,330
这么说吧 荣耀、国家、勇气
Well… honor, country, valor.

469
00:34:58,620 --> 00:35:01,700
这些必然是值得为之奋斗的崇高理念
These surely are worthwhile, elevated ideas by themselves,

470
00:35:01,790 --> 00:35:02,750
同意吧？
wouldn't you agree?

471
00:35:04,290 --> 00:35:06,370
然而 人们为了这些理念赴死
-Mm-hmm. -And nevertheless, men are dying for them.

472
00:35:07,040 --> 00:35:08,950
以一种显然毫不崇高的方式
In a decidedly un-elevated way,

473
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:11,910
脸埋在泥泞里 喉咙呛着血
face down in the mud, choking on blood,

474
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:13,200
痛得大喊大叫
screaming in pain.

475
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:17,370
他们是某人的父亲、兄弟或儿子
Men that were fathers, brothers or sons to someone out there.

476
00:35:17,450 --> 00:35:19,370
他们被自己的母亲带到这个世界
Men that were fed, cleaned and nursed

477
00:35:19,450 --> 00:35:21,330
被悉心喂养、洗净、照料、教育
and schooled into this world by their mothers,

478
00:35:21,910 --> 00:35:23,870
最后却被送到某个遥远的战场
only to fall on a battlefield far away,

479
00:35:23,950 --> 00:35:26,160
真正制造惨剧的人却躲得远远的
far from those that provoke these tragedies.

480
00:35:27,370 --> 00:35:31,290
他们好好地待在家中 不沾血 不挨刀
Those men remain at home, untouched by blood or bayonet,

481
00:35:32,410 --> 00:35:35,450
皮肤完好无损 被窝温暖洁净
their skin unpierced, their blankets warm and clean.

482
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:40,870
这就是蠢人追求理念的后果
That is what happens when ideas are pursued by fools.

483
00:35:40,950 --> 00:35:42,700
那你觉得我是蠢人
And you think me a fool?

484
00:35:43,540 --> 00:35:44,370
嗯?
Hmm?

485
00:35:46,330 --> 00:35:47,910
快享用你的白兰地和雪茄去吧
Run to your brandy and cigars.

486
00:35:48,580 --> 00:35:49,910
他们都在等着呢
The boys are waiting.

487
00:35:56,330 --> 00:36:01,160
一个人常常以为遇见了天使或魔鬼
How often a man believes he's met an angel or a devil,

488
00:36:02,660 --> 00:36:04,910
到头来却发现一切不过是幻觉
only to find it is all an illusion.

489
00:36:07,950 --> 00:36:09,500
我们下的这盘棋
The game of chess we play…

490
00:36:10,910 --> 00:36:12,750
对手只有自己
we play only against ourselves.

491
00:36:15,160 --> 00:36:16,000
帮帮他
Help him.

492
00:36:16,620 --> 00:36:17,580
快点！
Help him!

493
00:36:18,660 --> 00:36:20,500
给 喝点吧
Here you go. Drink some.

494
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:44,410
快跟我来
You better come with me.

495
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:47,200
什么都没有
Nothing.

496
00:36:47,290 --> 00:36:48,910
先生 看守人看到他了
Sir, the watchman saw him.

497
00:36:49,790 --> 00:36:51,450
在迷雾中绕着船转
Circling the ship. In the mist.

498
00:36:51,540 --> 00:36:53,160
我们都亲眼看他沉下去了
We all saw him drown.

499
00:36:53,250 --> 00:36:54,410
先生
Sir.

500
00:36:54,500 --> 00:36:56,000
大家都很恐慌
The men are terrified.

501
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:58,450
觉得该把那个男人扔到冰面上
They think that man should be surrendered to the ice

502
00:36:58,540 --> 00:36:59,700
结束这一切
and be done with this.

503
00:37:02,330 --> 00:37:04,000
他受我保护…
He is under my protection…

504
00:37:06,450 --> 00:37:08,080
受王国庇佑！
and the protection of the Crown!

505
00:37:21,830 --> 00:37:24,790
几周后 我、威廉和哈兰德 骑马穿过海峡
A few weeks later, I rode with William and Harlander

506
00:37:24,870 --> 00:37:27,450
来到瓦杜兹附近的一个湖边
to a lake near Vaduz across the channel.

507
00:37:27,540 --> 00:37:30,950
这座塔楼是用来过滤农田灌溉用水的
The tower was built as a water filtration plant to irrigate the fields.

508
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:33,910
是个公共工程项目 所以战争一开始就被弃建了
Public works, so construction was abandoned at the start of the war.

509
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:36,870
不是这场战争 是前一场
Not this war, the one before.

510
00:37:37,540 --> 00:37:39,660
或者是再前面一场 我记不清了
Or the one before that, I cannot quite remember.

511
00:37:44,500 --> 00:37:46,500
一看到它
The moment I laid eyes on it…

512
00:37:47,620 --> 00:37:48,620
这座塔楼
The tower.

513
00:37:49,370 --> 00:37:52,870
我便感受到了命运的召唤
I could feel destiny calling.

514
00:38:03,790 --> 00:38:05,580
建筑结构基本完整
The structure's basically intact.

515
00:38:05,660 --> 00:38:08,750
这里还有一条陡坡道 从顶上直通到底部
And there's a chute going from top, right to the bottom.

516
00:38:09,410 --> 00:38:11,200
我会安排人把你的个人物品
I can arrange for your belongings.

517
00:38:11,290 --> 00:38:13,160
从爱丁堡运过来
We'll bring them from Edinburgh.

518
00:38:26,950 --> 00:38:29,660
你需要什么 都能满足
Anything you need or want shall be granted.

519
00:38:30,540 --> 00:38:32,200
-什么都可以？ -什么都可以
-Anything? -Anything.

520
00:38:41,830 --> 00:38:45,370
整个项目期间 威廉随叫随到
I have secured William's service for the duration of the project.

521
00:38:45,450 --> 00:38:46,700
我要一个临时密室
I'll need a holding cell.

522
00:38:47,580 --> 00:38:49,500
-实验室旁边要有个冷库 -威廉
-And an ice chamber close to the lab. -William.

523
00:38:50,410 --> 00:38:52,790
塔楼底部有两个泵水库
There are two pump reservoirs at the base of the tower.

524
00:38:52,870 --> 00:38:54,290
要改造一下
We'll repurpose those.

525
00:38:54,370 --> 00:38:56,290
我们要重启蒸汽机
We shall need to recondition the steam engines.

526
00:38:56,370 --> 00:38:58,160
需要足够的燃料 来保证机器正常运转
We'll need enough fuel to make sure they run.

527
00:38:58,750 --> 00:39:02,410
那里 还有那里 放四块高容量的伏打电池
There and there, four high-capacity voltaic batteries,

528
00:39:02,500 --> 00:39:04,160
正负电极
positive and negative polarity,

529
00:39:04,250 --> 00:39:08,450
还要一套纯银避雷针系统 向下延伸至实验室
and a lightning rod system of pure silver telescoping down into the lab.

530
00:39:08,540 --> 00:39:13,540
没问题 你需要什么设备 我的承包商都能造出来
Yes. My contractors can manufacture any and all equipment you may require.

531
00:39:15,500 --> 00:39:18,000
那么 我们应该达成共识了吧？
I take it then that we have an understanding?

532
00:39:25,200 --> 00:39:26,750
交易达成
A bargain has been struck.

533
00:39:37,370 --> 00:39:38,370
混蛋！
Bastard!

534
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:41,120
这个不行
No. No. Not this one.

535
00:39:45,330 --> 00:39:46,250
张嘴
Aah. Open your mouth.

536
00:39:48,410 --> 00:39:51,540
被绞死算你走运 你本就活不过今年了
You, you're lucky to be hanged. You would have died within the year.

537
00:39:51,620 --> 00:39:54,120
哈兰德先生答应我 让我拿到最好的样本
Herr Harlander promised me access to optimal specimens.

538
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:55,870
阁下 他倒是答应了
Yeah, that he may have, your lordship,

539
00:39:55,950 --> 00:39:57,120
可您也知道
but as you well know,

540
00:39:58,370 --> 00:40:00,870
犯罪又不是什么好差事 我们这里也只有些歪瓜裂枣
crime doesn't pay, and it's a poor showing of it we have here.

541
00:40:00,950 --> 00:40:02,700
哪个都是可怜虫
They're wretches every one of them.

542
00:40:02,790 --> 00:40:03,950
真是抱歉
I'm sorry about that.

543
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:06,120
背很强壮 这个可以
That's a strong back. This one will do.

544
00:40:42,250 --> 00:40:43,290
稍后再来
Come back later.

545
00:40:43,370 --> 00:40:44,450
来告解？
Confession?

546
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:48,200
我很好奇
I was intrigued.

547
00:40:50,450 --> 00:40:54,750
如此纤弱又虔诚的人 能有什么要告解的？
What would such a delicate, pious creature have to confess to?

548
00:40:57,120 --> 00:41:00,540
真是碰巧 被我找到了一个机会
As luck would have it, an opportunity presented itself,

549
00:41:00,620 --> 00:41:01,620
我…
and I…

550
00:41:03,950 --> 00:41:05,660
我就要揭开谜底了
I was about to find out.

551
00:41:26,870 --> 00:41:28,700
神父 请为我祝福 我有罪
Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.

552
00:41:29,580 --> 00:41:33,250
孩子 你多久没告解了？
How long has it been since your last confession, my daughter?

553
00:41:33,330 --> 00:41:35,540
还没到一周 神父 我在修道院待过
Barely a week, Father. I was in a convent.

554
00:41:36,040 --> 00:41:37,120
就一周？
A week?

555
00:41:38,450 --> 00:41:40,580
你就这么轻率地犯错了？
Tsk-tsk. Have you so hastily committed sin?

556
00:41:40,660 --> 00:41:41,580
是的
I have.

557
00:41:42,080 --> 00:41:43,910
是罪孽的念头 并非实际行动
Sin of intent, not deed.

558
00:41:44,620 --> 00:41:46,620
-因为一名男子 对不对？ -对
-A man, is it? -Yes.

559
00:41:46,700 --> 00:41:47,950
是我未婚夫的兄长
My fiancé's brother.

560
00:41:49,500 --> 00:41:50,660
是欲念吗？
Lust?

561
00:41:50,750 --> 00:41:51,580
是憎恶
Hatred.

562
00:41:51,660 --> 00:41:52,500
憎恶…
Hatred…

563
00:41:53,450 --> 00:41:56,620
-憎恶？ -那名男子很恶劣、很丑陋
-Hatred? -The man is appalling, grotesque.

564
00:41:57,790 --> 00:41:59,290
这样的话很是刺耳
Harsh words.

565
00:41:59,370 --> 00:42:01,000
近乎无情了 对吗？
Rather uncharitable, wouldn't you say?

566
00:42:01,080 --> 00:42:03,540
尊敬的神父 您并不了解这个人
Respectfully, Father, you do not know this man.

567
00:42:03,620 --> 00:42:07,080
他试图操控周围一切的人和事
He tries to control and manipulate everything and everyone around him.

568
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:09,790
他和所有暴君一样 以假扮受害者为乐
Like every tyrant, he delights in playing the victim.

569
00:42:09,870 --> 00:42:11,290
要我说 那是他唯一的本事
His only advantage, I would say,

570
00:42:11,370 --> 00:42:13,830
他自以为绅士 实则粗鄙不堪
is he's far cruder than he believes himself to be.

571
00:42:14,870 --> 00:42:15,870
粗鄙不堪？
Cruder?

572
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:18,330
我的孩子 请详细说明
Uh, pray explain yourself, my child.

573
00:42:18,410 --> 00:42:21,080
比如说 他太容易被发现了
For one, he's easy to spot.

574
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:26,290
即便是集市日的拥挤街道上 也能轻松看到他
You can see him… even on a busy street on market day.

575
00:42:32,330 --> 00:42:34,040
说吧 你什么时候发现我的？
Tell me, how soon did you spot me?

576
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:37,040
只能说远比你看到我来得早
I saw you well before you saw me, I can say that much.

577
00:42:37,120 --> 00:42:38,160
你吃过晚饭了吗？
Have you had supper?

578
00:42:38,250 --> 00:42:40,000
我还不怎么饿 男爵 谢谢
I'm not that hungry, Baron. Thank you.

579
00:42:40,080 --> 00:42:41,540
我就饿坏了
Well, I for one am famished.

580
00:42:44,450 --> 00:42:46,540
-谢谢 好心人 -谢谢 先生
-Thank you, my good man. -Thank you, sir.

581
00:42:46,620 --> 00:42:48,910
你买了什么书？能让我看看吗？
What books did you buy, hmm? May I?

582
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:51,120
你猜
Guess.

583
00:42:51,790 --> 00:42:53,290
-让我猜？ -还是猜一下吧
-Guess? -Mm-hmm. I'd rather that you did.

584
00:42:53,370 --> 00:42:54,290
那好
Very well.

585
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,200
言情小说
A romance…

586
00:42:59,910 --> 00:43:04,160
沐浴着地中海的阳光 身着丝绸华服 沉醉于爱的纠葛
drenched in Mediterranean sun and silk and the skirmishes of love.

587
00:43:04,250 --> 00:43:06,700
真是无礼 但也不奇怪
Insulting, but unsurprising.

588
00:43:07,790 --> 00:43:08,790
是吗？
Really?

589
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:16,160
昆虫？
-Insects? -Mm.

590
00:43:17,660 --> 00:43:20,540
我对科学的兴趣 体现在对微小生物的好奇上
My interest in science leans towards the smallest things.

591
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:23,950
它们随自然而动 或许是顺应上帝的节律
Moving with nature, perhaps the rhythms of God.

592
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:29,410
我一直在寻觅 某种更纯粹、更奇妙的事物
I've always searched for something more pure, marvelous.

593
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:35,200
这就是你在修道院追寻的东西吗？
Is that what you were seeking in the convent?

594
00:43:37,910 --> 00:43:38,950
算是吧
In a way.

595
00:43:41,120 --> 00:43:42,120
值得吗？
Was it worth it?

596
00:43:43,950 --> 00:43:44,950
有什么是值得的吗？
Is anything?

597
00:43:54,120 --> 00:43:55,700
可以吗？
Permit me, sister.

598
00:44:00,200 --> 00:44:01,620
这样好像不大合适
This hardly seems appropriate.

599
00:44:02,200 --> 00:44:03,250
有什么是合适的吗？
Is anything?

600
00:44:07,830 --> 00:44:08,870
很好
Very well.

601
00:44:19,370 --> 00:44:20,580
笑起来！
Laughter!

602
00:44:23,000 --> 00:44:24,620
生平第一次
And for the very first time,

603
00:44:25,500 --> 00:44:27,620
不知何故 我对生的兴趣渐浓
I became more interested in life

604
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:30,950
对死的兴趣
and somewhat less interested

605
00:44:31,040 --> 00:44:32,160
减淡了
in death.

606
00:44:50,870 --> 00:44:55,290
主杆采用快速螺栓固定系统
The main rod has a fast bolting system.

607
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:57,330
用合金了吗？
Did you use an alloy?

608
00:44:58,330 --> 00:44:59,870
铜锌合金
Copper and zinc.

609
00:44:59,950 --> 00:45:02,750
这个不行 重来吧
This is… This simply will not do. Start over.

610
00:45:03,540 --> 00:45:05,160
纯银是完美的导体
Pure silver is a perfect conductor.

611
00:45:06,910 --> 00:45:09,120
威廉 你得留下 拜托了
William, you must stay behind. Please.

612
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:11,120
我最信任的就是你了
I trust you above anyone else.

613
00:45:11,200 --> 00:45:12,410
再多待几天就行
Only for a few more days.

614
00:45:20,250 --> 00:45:22,120
你抓不到它的
You're not going to catch her.

615
00:45:27,830 --> 00:45:30,500
真漂亮
Beautiful. Beautiful.

616
00:45:30,580 --> 00:45:32,830
把它关起来 还是放走呢？
-Should we trap her or let her go? -Mm…

617
00:45:32,910 --> 00:45:33,750
关起来
Trap her.

618
00:45:36,370 --> 00:45:38,080
这下我们有共同点了
Now we have something in common.

619
00:45:39,790 --> 00:45:40,790
一个囚徒
A prisoner.

620
00:45:41,290 --> 00:45:46,200
威廉如约行事 认真负责建造实验室 满足各种需求
As promised, William took dutiful charge of the laboratory build and needs.

621
00:45:48,370 --> 00:45:49,830
那边能修一下吗？
Can you fix that over there, please?

622
00:45:50,500 --> 00:45:51,330
去帮一下
Go, help.

623
00:45:52,450 --> 00:45:55,120
他严格按我的指示办事
He followed my instructions to the letter.

624
00:45:57,660 --> 00:45:58,700
电池
The battery.

625
00:46:07,580 --> 00:46:09,040
现在是纯银的了
It's all pure silver now.

626
00:46:09,700 --> 00:46:13,120
这是和淋巴系统相对应的传导点
Conduction points corresponding to the lymphatic system,

627
00:46:14,250 --> 00:46:18,200
非常复杂 但我做出来了
which was quite complex. -But I managed.

628
00:46:17,330 --> 00:46:19,250
嗯哼
Mm-hmm.

629
00:46:59,790 --> 00:47:03,000
哈兰德先生 谢谢 派对很精彩
Herr Harlander, thank you. The party's delightful.

630
00:47:03,080 --> 00:47:06,120
但愿我们没有干扰你做研究
I hope we're not distracting you from your research

631
00:47:07,620 --> 00:47:09,790
毕竟你还要顾着我和伊丽莎白
to tend to me and Elizabeth.

632
00:47:11,540 --> 00:47:12,540
完全没有
Not at all.

633
00:47:12,620 --> 00:47:16,000
她还年轻 我们得护着她
She's young. She can count on us to guard her.

634
00:47:19,750 --> 00:47:21,450
我还是回避一下
I shall leave you your privacy.

635
00:47:21,540 --> 00:47:23,830
我们之间还掩饰什么
No need for subterfuge between us.

636
00:47:26,290 --> 00:47:29,540
法国陶瓷 多么美妙的共响
French porcelain, chimes to a man's stream.

637
00:47:31,120 --> 00:47:35,370
我快找到解决方法了 给淋巴系统确定传导点
I am very near a solution, an access point to the lymphatic system.

638
00:47:35,450 --> 00:47:37,160
哦 那个呀
Ah, yeah, that.

639
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:39,160
这么久了
It's been so long.

640
00:47:41,410 --> 00:47:43,120
仗快打完了
The war is waning.

641
00:47:45,040 --> 00:47:47,160
资金供应也快断了
And my funding will end with it.

642
00:47:47,250 --> 00:47:49,700
你不是说资金无限供应吗？
You said your funds were unlimited.

643
00:47:49,790 --> 00:47:51,120
但我的耐心是有限的
My patience is not.

644
00:47:52,040 --> 00:47:55,750
我得到了可靠消息 一周内会爆发一场战斗
I have it on good authority that a battle is to take place within a week.

645
00:47:57,790 --> 00:48:00,950
战争好比潮水 会把战利品送到我们这条海岸上来
The tide of war will deliver its bounty to our shore.

646
00:48:01,040 --> 00:48:03,200
战场上的尸体肯定一塌糊涂
A battlefield? The bodies will be mangled.

647
00:48:03,290 --> 00:48:04,200
就一周
One week.

648
00:48:05,120 --> 00:48:08,080
-一周？ -一周后 创造历史的机会就会溜走
-One week? -After that, history will pass us by.

649
00:48:10,660 --> 00:48:12,950
帮我冲一下吧 男爵
Flush that for me, will you, Baron?

650
00:48:15,580 --> 00:48:19,370
一周内找到传递电流的办法
A week to determine how to deliver the current.

651
00:48:19,450 --> 00:48:20,410
绝无可能
Impossible.

652
00:48:21,580 --> 00:48:22,830
我该怎么办？
What would I do?

653
00:48:22,910 --> 00:48:24,830
就快成功了 我感觉得到
I was close. I could feel it.

654
00:48:25,580 --> 00:48:29,500
谁知横生阻碍
And then…life got in the way.

655
00:48:29,580 --> 00:48:30,580
哦
Oh.

656
00:48:32,450 --> 00:48:33,870
它肯定想你了
I believe she missed you.

657
00:48:35,250 --> 00:48:37,910
伊丽莎白 我得先警告你一下 我在处理解剖体
I must warn you, Elizabeth, I've been working on a dissection.

658
00:48:38,000 --> 00:48:39,040
很美
It's beautiful.

659
00:48:41,830 --> 00:48:42,910
吓到你了吗？
Does it shock you?

660
00:48:43,870 --> 00:48:46,250
让我想起了殉道主题的绘画
Reminds me of martyrdom paintings.

661
00:48:49,700 --> 00:48:50,620
没有了痛苦
Pain is gone.

662
00:48:52,200 --> 00:48:55,370
在对称的构造和形状中 看得到上帝的精妙手笔
You can see God's design in the symmetry and the shapes.

663
00:48:57,790 --> 00:48:58,620
伊丽莎白
Elizabeth.

664
00:49:00,790 --> 00:49:02,580
我得向你坦白
I must confess something to you.

665
00:49:04,500 --> 00:49:07,580
我相信这世间存在奇妙非凡之物 你也一样
I have a belief in the marvelous and so do you.

666
00:49:09,620 --> 00:49:12,040
我们之间有种默契 你能感觉到吗？
There is a bond between us. Can you feel it?

667
00:49:12,120 --> 00:49:15,750
一种近乎生理上的吸引 我坚信这种感觉绝非寻常
An almost physical one. I truly believe it to be something else.

668
00:49:24,040 --> 00:49:26,200
你所信之物 未必是事实
Believing something does not make it true.

669
00:49:30,370 --> 00:49:31,580
那你为什么来这里？
Then why are you here?

670
00:49:39,160 --> 00:49:41,250
它很美 对不对？
Beautiful creature, is she not?

671
00:49:43,080 --> 00:49:47,330
孤傲 令人沉迷 却又如此怪异
Remote. Entirely bewitching, but so odd.

672
00:49:53,080 --> 00:49:54,160
有三颗心
Three hearts.

673
00:49:55,120 --> 00:49:56,910
复眼 白色的血
Multiple eyes. White blood.

674
00:49:59,000 --> 00:50:01,370
它无法做出选择 所以如此迷人
And a fascinating lack of choice.

675
00:50:01,950 --> 00:50:03,080
我不明白
I don't understand.

676
00:50:04,450 --> 00:50:06,330
有选择的能力 灵魂才能栖息
Choice is the seat of the soul.

677
00:50:09,040 --> 00:50:10,950
这是上帝对我们的赠礼
The one gift God granted us.

678
00:50:16,120 --> 00:50:17,200
伊丽莎白
Elizabeth…

679
00:50:21,540 --> 00:50:22,540
我做出选择了
I have chosen.

680
00:50:23,040 --> 00:50:24,120
晚安
Good night.

681
00:50:30,790 --> 00:50:31,750
伊丽莎白！
Elizabeth!

682
00:50:35,040 --> 00:50:35,870
伊丽莎白！
Elizabeth!

683
00:50:40,410 --> 00:50:41,660
我以为我失败了
I thought I had failed.

684
00:50:43,250 --> 00:50:45,500
以为一切都完了 以为…
I thought it was entirely over. I thought…

685
00:50:46,950 --> 00:50:48,000
我以为…
And I thought…

686
00:50:49,160 --> 00:50:50,000
我…
And I…

687
00:50:50,950 --> 00:50:52,250
对称性
The symmetry.

688
00:50:58,620 --> 00:51:00,750
上帝创造的对称性 对
God's symmetry. Yes, yes.

689
00:51:14,120 --> 00:51:15,000
找到了
Yes.

690
00:51:29,250 --> 00:51:31,540
把电池放在淋巴系统上
Placing the battery above the lymphatic system.

691
00:51:32,160 --> 00:51:33,950
我就这么找到了解题的关键
I had found the key.

692
00:51:34,660 --> 00:51:36,410
再也没有什么能阻挡我了
Nothing could stop me now.

693
00:51:38,620 --> 00:51:39,540
没有
Nothing.

694
00:51:42,410 --> 00:51:44,540
别动！这堆尸体
No! No, do not take any bodies

695
00:51:44,620 --> 00:51:47,790
顶上的和底部的都别搬 就搬我做了标记的
from the top or the bottom of the pile unless I mark them.

696
00:51:47,870 --> 00:51:50,080
冰冻或腐败可能会破坏组织
Ice or rot may have destroyed the tissue.

697
00:51:50,950 --> 00:51:52,160
就看中间的那些
Look only in the middle.

698
00:51:58,750 --> 00:52:02,620
东西太多 会让人晕头转向 除非目标非常明确
Abundance can be disorienting unless one hones one's aim.

699
00:52:02,700 --> 00:52:05,450
我想要个子高的 长手长脚的
I'm favoring tall specimens, long limbs.

700
00:52:05,540 --> 00:52:07,290
划定范围 活就好干了
Scale will make the work easier.

701
00:52:07,370 --> 00:52:08,330
我喜欢
I like that.

702
00:52:10,330 --> 00:52:11,330
尽善尽美嘛
Perfection.

703
00:52:12,370 --> 00:52:14,200
有什么不好呢 亲爱的男爵？
And why not, dear Baron?

704
00:52:15,790 --> 00:52:17,120
确实 有什么不好呢？
Indeed, why not?

705
00:52:17,830 --> 00:52:19,450
找到完整的人头
Look for a head that's intact.

706
00:52:20,790 --> 00:52:21,830
搬到车上去
Put that one in the cart.

707
00:52:27,160 --> 00:52:28,370
那个放那边
Set that one over there.

708
00:52:28,870 --> 00:52:29,910
其他的送过来
Bring the others.

709
00:52:35,950 --> 00:52:36,870
老天
Oh, good God.

710
00:53:50,790 --> 00:53:51,910
劳驾
Do you mind?

711
00:55:19,250 --> 00:55:20,620
大功告成
It is finished.

712
00:56:05,620 --> 00:56:06,830
哈兰德先生！
Herr Harlander!

713
00:56:07,910 --> 00:56:09,200
暴风雨要来了！
A storm is coming!

714
00:56:12,040 --> 00:56:12,870
我的拐杖
My cane.

715
00:56:14,370 --> 00:56:15,200
我的拐杖！
My cane!

716
00:56:15,790 --> 00:56:17,120
我的拐杖 手柄打开
My cane, in the handle.

717
00:56:26,790 --> 00:56:27,700
水银
Mercury.

718
00:56:27,790 --> 00:56:29,500
-你病了吗？ -谢谢
-Are you ill? -Thank you.

719
00:56:40,540 --> 00:56:42,580
是梅毒吗？
Is it… syphilis?

720
00:56:45,370 --> 00:56:46,540
对 我快死了
Yeah, I'm dying.

721
00:56:48,700 --> 00:56:51,700
一夜偷欢 终生服毒
One night with Venus, a lifetime with Mercury.

722
00:56:51,790 --> 00:56:52,910
是这么说的吧？
Isn't that the phrase?

723
00:56:53,660 --> 00:56:54,700
几期了？
What stage?

